<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="253" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="253">
Although 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. madecassus" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="species" species="madecassus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z. madecassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. seyrigi" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were the only representatives of 
<taxonomicName authority="" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. (Madecazethus)" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Madecazethus">Z. (Madecazethus)</taxonomicName>
they are not sister groups and thus, should not be placed in a species group of their own. A wider analysis of the African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes &amp; Carpenter &amp; Noll" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Zethus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zethus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Zethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is needed to verify the validity of the already proposed 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">pubescens</emphasis>
group (represented by 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. empeyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="species" species="empeyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z. empeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. rhodani" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="species" species="rhodani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z. rhodani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. rotschildianus" pageId="0" pageNumber="253" rank="species" species="rotschildianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="253">Z. rotschildianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), since it may also be paraphyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
